'''The China International Gallery Exposition''' (aka '''CIGE''', Zhongguo guoji hualang bolanhui) is an annual [[art exhibition]] held in [[China]] which showcases modern art and design.

First held in April 2004 at the International Science and Technology Centre in [[Beijing]],<ref name="HungWang2010">{{cite book|author1=Wu Hung|author2=Peggy Wang|title=Contemporary Chinese Art: Primary Documents|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=UB1G9ekwydYC&pg=PT449|accessdate=5 March 2013|date=1 September 2010|publisher=The Museum of Modern Art|isbn=978-0-87070-647-9|page=449}}</ref><ref name=NTYART/> the CIGE had doubled in size by the following year<ref>{{cite news|last=Lubelski|first=Abraham|title=China Today: Chinese International Gallery Exposition|url=http://www.nyartsmagazine.com/july-august-2005/china-today-chinese-international-gallery-exposition-abraham-lubelski|accessdate=5 March 2013|newspaper=NY Arts Magazine|date=July 2005}}</ref>  and is now in its tenth iteration,{{Update after|2013|08|01}} which was held at the China National Convention Centre in April 2013.<ref>{{cite web|title=CIGE 2013 New Venue Brings Fresh Experience|url=http://www.cige-bj.com/news_en/12515FD602.html|publisher=CIGE|accessdate=5 March 2013}}</ref> In 2007 a spin-off festival, Art Beijing, emerged as a separate event.<ref name=NTYART>{{cite news|last=Chen|first=Xhingyu|title=Art Fairs Are Giving New Prestige to Asia|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2011/12/03/arts/03iht-rartfairs03.html?_r=0|accessdate=5 March 2013|newspaper=New York Times|date=2 December 2011}}</ref>

